<title>New Download</title>
<p>This page explains all options for configuring a new download in <app>Parabolic</app>.</p>

<terms>
    <item>
      <title>URL del media</title>
      <p>The URL of the media to download. Must be a valid ("valid" meaning syntactically correct) http or https link.</p>
      <note>
            <p>If a valid URL is found inside the clipboard upon opening the Add Download dialog, the URL will be automatically pasted in the URL entry row.</p>
      </note>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Autenticazione</title>
      <p>If enabled, the user will be asked to provide a username and/or password to pass to yt-dlp when downloading.</p>
        <p>If keyring is enabled, the user will be asked to chose from a list of named credentials or can chose to enter manually a different username and/or password.</p>
		<note style="advanced">
			<p>Not all websites support passing usernames and passwords to yt-dlp. For example, YouTube does NOT support this feature.</p>
            <p>For these sites that don't support passing credentials, it is recommended to upload a Cookies file in Preferences instead.</p>
		</note>
    </item>
    <item>
		<title>Tipo di file</title>
		<p>The file type of which to download the media as.</p>
            <p>If <code>Disallow Conversions</code> is enabled, the only options will be <code>Video</code> (if supported) and <code>Audio</code></p>
        <note>
            <p>The previously used file type will be remembered and pre-selected for the next download.</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
		<title>QualitÃ </title>
		<p>If the file type is a video type, the listed qualities will be the resolutions of the media available.</p>
        <p>If the file type is an audio type, the listed qualities will be simply <code>Best</code> and <code>Worst</code>.</p>
        <note>
            <p>The previously used quality will be remembered and pre-selected for the next download.</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
		<title>Download Subtitle</title>
		<p>Whether to download and embed subtitle when downloading a video. Languages for subtitles can be defined in <link xref="downloader">preferences</link>.</p>
        <note>
            <p>The previously used state will be remembered and pre-selected for the next download.</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
		<title>Cartella di salvataggio</title>
		<p>The folder at which to save the download to.</p>
        <p>If the file type is an audio type, the listed qualities will be simply <code>Best</code> and <code>Worst</code>.</p>
        <note>
            <p>The previously used folder will be remembered and pre-selected for the next download.</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
		<title>Limite di velocitÃ </title>
		<p>If enabled, Parabolic will limit the download's speed with the speed configured in Preferences.</p>
        <note>
            <p>Available in the <code>Advanced Options</code> section.</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
        <title>Dividi i capitoli</title>
        <p>If enabled, Parabolic will split the video into multiple smaller ones based on its chapters.</p>
        <note>
            <p>Available in the <code>Advanced Options</code> section.</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
		<title>Crop Thumbnail</title>
        <p>Only available if <code>Embed Metadata</code> is enabled in Preferences.</p>
		<p>If enabled, Parabolic will crop a download's embedded thumbnail as square. This is useful when downloading music who's album images are usually square.</p>
        <note>
            <p>Available in the <code>Advanced Options</code> section.</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
		<title>Scarica intervallo specifico</title>
		<p>If enabled, the user will be able to enter a start timeframe and an end timeframe for a section of the media to download.</p>
        <note>
            <p>Available in the <code>Advanced Options</code> section.</p>
        </note>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Enablining this option will disable the use of aria2 as the downloader for this download if it is enabled in Preferences.</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
		<title>File Name</title>
        <p>The file name to use when saving the download.</p>
		<note style="advanced">
			<p>Default: The title of the media</p>
		</note>
    </item>
</terms>
